[SN]TITLE[SN]
Woman dies following suspected West Didsbury hit-and-run

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A woman has died following a suspected hit-and-run in Manchester.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Two women were hit by a van at a pedestrian crossing in Princess Parkway, West Didsbury, on 16 January.
A 57-year-old woman has died from her injuries and a woman aged 70 remains in a serious but stable condition.
Two men arrested on suspicion of causing serious injury by dangerous driving and failing to stop at the scene of a collision have been released on bail.
Sgt Mark Thomas said: "Tragically, one of the women has now died from her injuries while the other remains in a serious condition in hospital.
"We are continuing to support their families through this difficult time."
